This guide walks you through the installation and configuration of OpenVPN Access Server on an AWS EC2 instance within a custom VPC.

âš™ï¸ Prerequisites

AWS account with permissions to create VPC, subnets, EC2 instances, and security groups

Basic knowledge of Linux commands and SSH

OpenVPN official installation script

ğŸ—ï¸ Step 1: Create a VPC

Set up a VPC with the following configuration:

VPC: 1

Public Subnets: 2 ğŸŒ

Private Subnets: 2 ğŸ”’

Internet Gateway (IGW): 1

NAT Gateway: 1

Ensure your route tables are configured correctly so that public subnets can access the Internet via IGW and private subnets via NAT.

ğŸ’» Step 2: Launch an EC2 Instance

Launch a public EC2 instance in one of the public subnets.

Assign a public IP to the instance for remote access ğŸŒ.

Connect to the instance via SSH ğŸ”‘.

ğŸ› ï¸ Step 3: Install OpenVPN Access Server

Run the following commands to update your instance and install OpenVPN Access Server:

sudo apt update
sudo bash -c 'bash <(curl -fsS https://packages.openvpn.net/as/install.sh) --yes'


This installs OpenVPN Access Server from the official OpenVPN repository âœ….

ğŸ“„ Step 4: Verify Installation

After installation, you should see output similar to:

